Acceptance: Room requests reuse existing GitHub-originated runner/work-item semantics for isolation, runner selection, acknowledgement, cancellation, retry, progress, blocked, and completion. Code-changing runs require the confirmed flow from T001. PR creation is allowed only from an explicitly supplied branch or the branch/result produced by that confirmed code-work operation, with target and head displayed before confirmation. Background permission is separate, duplicate idempotency keys do not start duplicate work or PRs, durable progress/results land in the anchored thread, and receipts plus resulting PR webhooks reconcile without loops. Tests cover confirmed success, rejection, stale branch/result, cancellation, duplicate invocation, PR creation, receipts, and reconciliation. Canonical contract: docs/plans/2026-07-12-github-item-room-routing.md.